column1: # This file is an extension for the 'parameterDef_fmi.csv' file. In this file
# we are definining FMI parameters that have the same name as the newbase
# parameters.
# This means that we can easily map Newbase parameters to FMI parameters without
# any conversion. We can even ignore the "standard" FMI parameters and use only
# these names.
# However, it is good to realize that there are good reasons why we use FMI parameter
# names in the first place. The point is that we try to harmonize and simplify
# the parameter identification.
# For example, it does not make sense that we have different parameter names for
# temperature on different levels (temperature,temperature-2m, temperature-10m, etc.).
# On the other hand we should have different parameter names for parameters that are
# using different units. For example, a temperature parameter expressed in Kelvins is
# a different parameter than a temperature parameter expressed in Celsius. So, if
# we just request a temperature parameter, we could get the temperature value
# in Kelvins, Celsius, Fahrenheit, etc. if we do not specify also the parameter
# unit.
# So, in spite of that we are able to define all kinds of FMI parameter names,
# we should use these names only "special cases".
# FIELDS:
# 1) FmiParameterId
# 2) FmiParameterName
# 3) FmiParameterUnits
# 4) FmiParameterDescription
# 5) AreaInterpolationMethod
# 6) TimeInterpolationMethod
# 7) LevelInterpolationMethod
# 8) DefaultPrecision
